  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Running of 6 mobile health teams to address the critical and urgent needs of health care services for the drought affected population in the 3 priority districts of Nimroz Province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of the project is to provide drought affected communities with emergency health services and psychosocial support to tackle with their critical and urgent needs. The beneficiaries will be the host communities, but also IDPs and returnees.  

To achieve these objective, MRCA propose to be in charge of the running of 6 Mobile Health Team: 2 in the district of Kang, 2 in the district of Chakhansor and 2 in the district of Chamburjak. These 3 districts have identified are primary priority districts according to the health cluster. 

MRCA will be in charge on the overall management of the project ensuring that the 6 MHTs have a complete and competent medical team (i.e 1 midwife, 1 medical doctor / nurse, vaccinator and 2 Psychological First Aid providers: 1 male and 1 female), following the MOPH guidelines and will ensure a global monitoring and date compilation. The MHTs will mainly focus on treatment or referral of the most common health problem present in drought affected areas (diarrhea, ARI, measles, snake bites, mental illness, etc&#x2026;).  

The main services delivered through the MHTs will be: 
-	Primary health care (PHC) with a special focus on mother and child health, by ensuring the presence of one midwife in the MHTs
-	Provision of EPI services
-	Surveillance of vaccine preventable, DEWS and outbreak management
-	Psychological first aid (PFA)

In order to ensure the quality of delivered health services by the MHTs, the capacity of the recruited staff will be reinforced through various training on HMIS, infection prevention, EPI and disease warning system.   Weekly supervision will verify the efficiency of the services in place.</narrative>
  </description>
